# Workspace Security Policy
_Last updated: [DATE]_

## The One Rule
Secrets live in `.env` locally and platform env vars in production. Nowhere else.
**Do not create a `secrets.md`.** Any file with "secrets" in the name is a high-value target â€” accidental commits, cloud sync, and AI context leakage all become risks.

---

## Where Secrets Live

| Environment | Location | Notes |
|-------------|----------|-------|
| Local dev | `.env` (gitignored) | Never commit |
| Vercel / Netlify | Platform env vars UI | Set manually per environment |
| GitHub Actions | Repository â†’ Settings â†’ Secrets | `${{ secrets.MY_KEY }}` |
| AWS | AWS Secrets Manager or Parameter Store | |

