## Claude Agent Rules

- Claude **CANNOT** edit `.env` files â€” blocked by PreToolUse hook in `settings.json`
- Claude **CAN** read `.env.example` (safe â€” placeholder values only)
- Claude **SHOULD** invoke `/security-scanner` before reading or using any file from an external source

---

## Protections In Place

| Layer | What it does | File |
|-------|-------------|------|
| `.gitignore` per project | Blocks `.env` from git staging | `project/.gitignore` |
| `~/.gitignore_global` | Blocks `.env` in ALL repos on this machine | `~/.gitignore_global` |
| PreToolUse hook | Claude cannot modify `.env` files | `~/.claude/settings.json` |
| Gitleaks pre-commit | Scans staged files for key patterns before every commit | `.pre-commit-config.yaml` |
| `security-scan.py` hook | Auto-scans files Claude reads from untrusted paths | `~/.claude/hooks/security-scan.py` |
| `tool-audit.py` hook | Logs every tool Claude calls, flags anomalous activity | `~/.claude/hooks/tool-audit.py` |
| `memory-drift-check.py` | Scans memory files for injected instructions at session start | `~/.claude/hooks/memory-drift-check.py` |
| `/security-scanner` skill | Full 5-step scan of external content on demand | `~/.claude/skills/security-scanner.md` |

---

## Incident Response

1. **Revoke immediately** â€” go to the provider dashboard and revoke the exposed key
2. **Rotate** â€” generate a new key, update `.env` locally and platform env vars
3. **If committed to git:**
   ```bash
   git filter-repo --path .env --invert-paths
   git push --force   # confirm with team first
   ```
4. **Audit** â€” check `~/.claude/tool-audit.log` for any suspicious activity around the incident time
5. **Post-mortem** â€” update this file with what changed

---

## Rotation Schedule

- Rotate immediately if: key committed to git, key seen in logs, breach suspected
- Rotate quarterly as standard practice

---

## New Project Checklist

When starting any new project:
- [ ] Create `.gitignore` with `.env` entries
- [ ] Create `.env.example` with placeholder values only
- [ ] Copy `.pre-commit-config-template.yaml` and run `pre-commit install`
- [ ] Document project secrets in this file (var names only, never values)
- [ ] Run `/security-scanner` on any external dependencies before integrating
